2.01	Pan_American_Exposition	Pan-American Exposition	The Pan-American Exposition was a World's Fair held in Buffalo, New York, United States, from May 1 through November 2, 1901. The fair occupied 350 acres (1.4 km2) of land on the western edge of what is present day Delaware Park, extending from Delaware Ave. to Elmwood Ave and northward to Great Arrow Ave.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Flickr_-_%E2%80%A6trialsanderrors_-_Pan-American_Exposition%2C_Buffalo%2C_1901.jpg/300px-Flickr_-_%E2%80%A6trialsanderrors_-_Pan-American_Exposition%2C_Buffalo%2C_1901.jpg
